										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>1 Cup/ 236.5 ML Red Lentils<br>1 Pound/ 0.453592 Kilograms Organic Grass Fed Ground Beef<br>.25 Cup/ 59.14 ML Minced Garlic<br>1 tsp/4.928 Organic Cumin<br>.5 tsp/ 2.464 ML Chili Powder<br>.5 tsp/ 2.464 ML Turmeric<br>.5 tsp/ 2.464 Celery Seed<br>.25 Cup/ 59.14 ML Lemon or Lime Juice<br>.25 Cup/ 59.14 ML Organic Apple Cider Vinegar<br>1 — 10 OZ/ 295.735 Can Rotel Tomatoes and Green Chilis<br>Salt and Pepper To Taste<br>Olive Oil, First Cold Press with Made on Date<br>.5 tsp/ 2.464 ML Grass fed Beef Bone Marrow Powder<br>1 Cup/ 236.5 ML filtered water</p>



<p>Prep time: 30 to 45 minutes<br>Feeds 2 to 4</p>



<p><strong>Tools:</strong><br><a href="https://amzn.to/3XAniNR" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">1 — 2.5 QT Stainless Steel Sauce Pan</a><br><a href="https://amzn.to/3lFAuDS" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">1 Bamboo Spoon</a><br><a href="https://amzn.to/3I35cOH" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Measuring Utensils</a></p>



<p><strong>Ingredients:</strong><br><a href="https://amzn.to/3jYI4sy" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Red Lentils</a><br><a href="https://amzn.to/3jXoxZy" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Grass Fed Beef</a><br><a href="https://amzn.to/3YPUAJN" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Minced Garlic</a><br><a href="https://amzn.to/3YV3Igq" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Organic Cumin</a><br><a href="https://amzn.to/3xo0S7A" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Chili Powder</a><br><a href="https://amzn.to/3YAcwZ2" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Turmeric</a><br><a href="https://amzn.to/3YPs6jk" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Celery Seed</a><br><a href="https://amzn.to/3YWYAs5" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Lemon</a> or <a href="https://amzn.to/3YWYAs5" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Lime Juice</a><br><a href="https://amzn.to/3YWYAs5" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Organic Apple Cider Vinegar</a><br><a href="https://amzn.to/3I385z9" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Rotel Tomatoes and Green Chilies</a><br><a href="https://amzn.to/3I5Dqkr" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Salt</a> and <a href="https://amzn.to/3E8jD2E" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Pepper</a><br><a href="https://amzn.to/3YwLXnv" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Bone Marrow Powder</a><br><a href="https://amzn.to/3K9XZPq" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Olive Oil</a><br><a href="https://amzn.to/3Iouvfw" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Filtered Water</a></p>



<p><strong>Directions:</strong><br>Pour a small amount of olive oil into sauce pan and heat to medium. Take 1 Pound/ 0.453592 Kilograms Organic Grass Fed Ground Beef and put into preheated pan. Break apart ground beef and turn up heat, sautéing beef.</p>



<p>Add minced garlic and continue to stir. Add lentils, cumin, chili powder, turmeric and celery seed. Add Rotel tomatoes and simmer.</p>



<p><strong>Add :</strong><br>In a separate container, combine lemon or lime juice and apple cider vinegar and water. Stir in bone marrow powder and let sit for 5 minutes. Incorporate a small amount of chili broth into liquids and slowly add liquids to chili. Let simmer until lentils are fully cooked, turn off heat and serve.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
